The paper proposes a framework for inference in large scale heterogeneous information networks using meta-paths and random walks. This involves machine learning techniques and data analysis, which are commonly associated with the sub-categories of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), databases (cs.DB), and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of semantic links and proximities between entities, which are relevant to the sub-category of information retrieval (cs.IR). Finally, the experiments are conducted on real-world datasets, which suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI).
